definition.value: A sandwich food product is a food product used to create a sandwich.  This includes bread as a container, and sandwich ingredients and spreads.
A soybean food product is a product derived from the soybean plant.
A food product made from spinach.
A food product deriving from one or more squashes.

definition.value: A water food product is a food product derived from H20 (water) in its liquid form.

SIREN DB annotation:
* has quality 'liquid, low viscosity, with no visible particles' (http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FOODON_03430123)
* has quality 'not heat-treated' (http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FOODON_03440003)
A meal type is the name of an eating occasion that may have location, food type, or other customary contextual features. (Damion's 1st draft definition)
A food product consisting of food material derived primarily from a single organism.
A food product traditionally consumed in the morning as the first meal of the day.
Any substance that can be consumed by an organism to satisfy nutritional or other health needs, or to provide a social or organoleptic food experience
This class is the top of FOODON's main food product hierarchy which is described in the https://www.foodon.org website, and can be searched in lookup services like https://www.ebi.ac.uk/ols/
